<HL> Business Brief: Suffield Financial Corp. </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<CO> SFCP </CO>
<IN> TNM </IN>
<TEXT>
   Milo L. Pike, a Tilton, N.H., businessman, said he holds a 9.2% stake in Suffield Financial Corp.'s common shares outstanding. 

   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mr. Pike said he holds 547,012 of the company's shares, including 546,962 purchased March 23 to May 18 for $7.9375 to $9.50 each. 

   According to the filing, Mr. Pike acquired the shares for investment purposes and may increase or decrease his holdings, depending on market and other factors. 

   In Suffield, Conn., a spokesman for the bank holding company said it was aware of the filing but had not yet received a copy and declined to comment further. 

